parameters.name: Purpose
parameters.description: indicates that this row contains science data

parameters.name: SCLOCK
parameters.description:
midpoint time of the averaging interval as a
                        spacecraft clock string; SCLOCK values are recorded as P/NNNNNNNNNN.FFF
                        where P is the partition number, NNNNNNNNNN is roughly the number of
                        seconds since the start of the partition, and FFF is the number of ticks.
                        Each tick is roughly 1/256 of a second.

parameters.name: Start_Ephemeris_s
parameters.description:
start time of the averaging interval in
                        ephemeris time (TDB seconds past the J2000 epoch)

parameters.name: End_Ephemeris_s
parameters.description:
end time of the averaging interval in
                        ephemeris time (TDB seconds past the J2000 epoch)

parameters.name: SZS_X
parameters.description:
SZS x component of the position of Cassini
                        relative to Saturn

parameters.name: SZS_Y
parameters.description:
SZS y component of the position of Cassini
                        relative to Saturn

parameters.name: SZS_Z
parameters.description:
SZS z component of the position of Cassini
                        relative to Saturn

parameters.name: MinSunAngle
parameters.description:
minimum angle between the LEMMS LET boresight
                        direction and the SC-to-Sun line during the averaging interval; this helps
                        users determine the possibility of light contamination; the most
                        conservative estimate is 60 degrees, but sometimes much smaller angles
                        such as 20 degrees are still ok
